  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6760.37 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6765 (-7.3B) and positive at 6800 (+5.9B), dealers are currently in buy-the-dip mode as they're short gamma at current levels. The recent wall break and GEX surge (57.1% 1-min spike) suggests increased volatility as we're testing the critical 6765 amplifying zone where dealer selling accelerates any downside momentum. Key inflection points are 6765 downside (major dealer buying kicks in) and 6800 upside (heavy dealer selling resistance).\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect volatile swings between 6765 support and 6800 resistance with dealers providing liquidity at both extremes.",
